Dreadnought Capital is an innovative South African financial services company dedicated to promoting growth in South Africa and Africa by leveraging its extensive expertise in capital markets.  

The services provided include:

-  the creation of sustainable, inclusive financial market ecosystems by creating derivatives exchanges, e.g. Bond and Derivatives Exchange (BaDEx) in Zambia.  

- A full turnkey consulting solution for successfully building exchanges, engaging with regulators, clearing banks and other stakeholders to ensure successful implementation;

- The creation forward-thinking and fully customised tradeable Indices, taking account of the unique factors that affect the African markets;

- South African derivatives trading in the Equities, Interest Rates and Commodities markets through its Resolution Market Management subsidiary, a member of the JSE SAFEX exchange;

- Derivatives structuring and consulting services for corporate and institutional clients across Africa.

NBG Securities Romania S.A. is a Romanian investment firm, subsidiary of National Bank of Greece (NBG) Group. 
The company was set up in 1996 under the name TOP Invest. After the acquisition of TOP Invest by Eteba Securities S.A., the Investment Banking arm of National Bank of Greece S.A., the company was renamed ETEBA Romania S.A. Further, following restructuring operations at Group level, the company become NBG Securities Romania in 2010).
NBG Securities Romania S.A. is a member and shareholder of the Bucharest Stock Exchange (BVB), Investors` Compensation Fund and Bucharest Clearing House and also a member of SIBEX Commodities Exchange and Brokers` Association.
NBG Securities Romania S.A. is authorised by the Romanian Securities Commission to provide the full object of activity as per MiFID Directive on investment services, such as: 
 Core services: 
- Reception and transmission of orders in relation to one or more financial instruments;
- Execution of orders on behalf of clients;
- Investment advice;
- Placing of financial instruments without a firm commitment;
